1
00:01:30,220 --> 00:01:32,980
Episode 05

2
00:01:34,870 --> 00:01:35,840
(I've read your resume.)

3
00:01:36,480 --> 00:01:36,950
(Credentials.)

4
00:01:37,840 --> 00:01:38,760
What credentials?

5
00:01:39,640 --> 00:01:41,280
Your diploma and certificates.

6
00:01:41,790 --> 00:01:43,230
Let me explain.

7
00:01:43,510 --> 00:01:45,120
I only completed three years

8
00:01:45,400 --> 00:01:46,510
and didn't get my degree.

9
00:01:46,870 --> 00:01:47,070
But...

10
00:01:47,070 --> 00:01:48,510
Then you don't meet our requirements.

11
00:01:49,150 --> 00:01:49,790
Next.

12
00:01:50,230 --> 00:01:50,840
Sir...

13
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:52,200
This isn't school.

14
00:01:52,510 --> 00:01:53,280
We're not your teacher.

15
00:01:53,590 --> 00:01:54,480
You used a fake resume

16
00:01:54,480 --> 00:01:55,560
and wasted our time.

17
00:01:55,950 --> 00:01:57,200
Be thankful I'm letting it go.

18
00:01:57,640 --> 00:01:58,120
Go out!

19
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:00,920
Next!

20
00:02:24,360 --> 00:02:25,240
(Even without)

21
00:02:25,240 --> 00:02:26,360
(a college degree,)

22
00:02:27,080 --> 00:02:27,960
(I still have)

23
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:29,520
(the qualities of a college graduate.)

24
00:02:30,150 --> 00:02:31,310
(Give me a chance,)

25
00:02:31,910 --> 00:02:33,030
(and I'll surprise you.)

26
00:02:50,400 --> 00:02:51,590
Having trouble finding a job?

27
00:02:52,960 --> 00:02:53,960
I know some places hiring.

28
00:02:54,710 --> 00:02:55,280
See if there's

29
00:02:55,560 --> 00:02:56,280
anything you like.

30
00:02:56,590 --> 00:02:57,240
Thanks.

31
00:03:05,310 --> 00:03:06,750
Your hair looks great.

32
00:03:07,080 --> 00:03:08,150
I had it done specially.

33
00:03:08,560 --> 00:03:09,240
Off to work?

34
00:03:09,470 --> 00:03:10,430
Gotta go, bye!

35
00:03:16,520 --> 00:03:17,150
See?

36
00:03:17,680 --> 00:03:18,150
I helped them

37
00:03:18,150 --> 00:03:19,150
find their jobs.

38
00:03:19,400 --> 00:03:20,430
They make good money now.

39
00:03:20,910 --> 00:03:22,000
A few days on the job,

40
00:03:22,750 --> 00:03:23,960
and they got their own spots.

41
00:03:24,750 --> 00:03:26,800
Do I look like I'd do that kind of work?

42
00:03:27,960 --> 00:03:29,000
Sure!

43
00:03:29,430 --> 00:03:30,800
You're pretty and innocent.

44
00:03:31,680 --> 00:03:32,630
You're just the type

45
00:03:32,910 --> 00:03:33,910
they're looking for now.

46
00:03:34,560 --> 00:03:35,190
Trust me.

47
00:03:35,430 --> 00:03:36,960
Just smile at the customers,

48
00:03:37,280 --> 00:03:38,910
and the tips won't stop.

49
00:03:40,400 --> 00:03:40,910
Finder's fee

50
00:03:40,960 --> 00:03:41,750
is half

51
00:03:41,750 --> 00:03:42,590
of your first salary.

52
00:03:42,960 --> 00:03:44,190
Tips are all yours.

53
00:03:45,590 --> 00:03:46,120
Check out.

54
00:03:47,840 --> 00:03:48,520
Check out!

55
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:09,510
You scratched out the number.

56
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:10,430
How do we

57
00:05:10,430 --> 00:05:11,480
reach you?

58
00:05:11,830 --> 00:05:12,680
I'm right here.

59
00:05:12,870 --> 00:05:14,430
If I meet your requirements,

60
00:05:14,560 --> 00:05:16,160
just give me a shot now.

61
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:18,040
Some college, no degree?

62
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:19,560
No way.

63
00:05:21,160 --> 00:05:21,950
Next.

64
00:05:23,630 --> 00:05:24,040
Hello.

65
00:05:24,430 --> 00:05:25,830
Here for the Finance Manager position.

66
00:05:26,870 --> 00:05:27,920
Fang Wanzhi!

67
00:05:34,750 --> 00:05:35,600
We meet again.

68
00:05:36,190 --> 00:05:37,310
How do you know my name?

69
00:05:42,560 --> 00:05:43,600
How did you get that?

70
00:05:43,630 --> 00:05:45,120
This resume's got style.

71
00:05:45,360 --> 00:05:46,560
Everyone was laughing at it.

72
00:05:46,950 --> 00:05:47,680
So they

73
00:05:47,720 --> 00:05:48,600
showed me.

74
00:05:50,160 --> 00:05:51,240
Don't grab!

75
00:05:51,430 --> 00:05:52,240
I'm keeping this.

76
00:05:52,360 --> 00:05:53,600
To show my students

77
00:05:53,630 --> 00:05:54,510
what not to do.

78
00:05:57,800 --> 00:05:58,800
Now do you see

79
00:05:58,830 --> 00:06:00,000
how important a degree is?

80
00:06:00,240 --> 00:06:00,870
So,

81
00:06:01,040 --> 00:06:01,920
come to our school.

82
00:06:02,160 --> 00:06:02,830
It starts this month.

83
00:06:02,920 --> 00:06:03,800
Five associate's,

84
00:06:03,920 --> 00:06:04,510
three bachelor's.

85
00:06:04,630 --> 00:06:06,510
Lowest tuition in Shenzhen.

86
00:06:07,040 --> 00:06:08,360
This is a job fair.

87
00:06:08,560 --> 00:06:09,720
But you're recruiting.

88
00:06:09,830 --> 00:06:10,920
That's fraud.

89
00:06:11,270 --> 00:06:12,430
Why would you say that?

90
00:06:12,750 --> 00:06:13,630
Many come here

91
00:06:13,720 --> 00:06:15,240
and realize degrees matter.

92
00:06:15,390 --> 00:06:16,160
Besides,

93
00:06:16,360 --> 00:06:17,680
our school is registered

94
00:06:17,680 --> 00:06:18,390
with the job fair.

95
00:06:18,390 --> 00:06:19,600
How can you call that fraud?

96
00:06:19,750 --> 00:06:21,360
We're helping those in need.

97
00:06:21,510 --> 00:06:22,480
Don't need it.

98
00:06:22,720 --> 00:06:23,830
I need a job.

99
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:25,430
But the way things stand,

100
00:06:25,480 --> 00:06:26,920
you can't find one.

101
00:06:27,240 --> 00:06:28,310
Are you cursing me?

102
00:06:28,680 --> 00:06:29,920
So many migrant workers get jobs.

103
00:06:29,920 --> 00:06:31,040
Why not me?

104
00:06:31,390 --> 00:06:32,630
Wanna be a migrant worker?

105
00:06:33,040 --> 00:06:34,270
Then you're in the wrong place.

106
00:06:34,510 --> 00:06:35,430
This job fair

107
00:06:35,480 --> 00:06:37,160
is for highly educated people.

108
00:06:37,750 --> 00:06:38,750
I'll go elsewhere.

109
00:06:39,430 --> 00:06:41,360
It's no use.

110
00:06:42,430 --> 00:06:43,510
Are you insane?

111
00:06:43,830 --> 00:06:45,190
Migrant workers in Shenzhen

112
00:06:45,270 --> 00:06:46,040
come in two types.

113
00:06:46,160 --> 00:06:46,720
First type:

114
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:47,720
strong and hardworking.

115
00:06:47,750 --> 00:06:48,560
Assembly line

116
00:06:48,600 --> 00:06:49,600
or construction.

117
00:06:49,720 --> 00:06:50,920
That's backbreaking.

118
00:06:50,920 --> 00:06:51,870
I can handle hardship.

119
00:06:52,600 --> 00:06:54,390
These workers were in demand before.

120
00:06:54,430 --> 00:06:55,870
But last year, Shenzhen changed

121
00:06:55,950 --> 00:06:56,830
its policies.

122
00:06:57,190 --> 00:06:58,630
Labor-intensive businesses

123
00:06:58,680 --> 00:06:59,560
are moving out.

124
00:06:59,630 --> 00:07:00,680
Fewer of those jobs now.

125
00:07:00,750 --> 00:07:02,360
Skilled workers are
waiting for new jobs.

126
00:07:02,430 --> 00:07:03,560
You have no chance.

127
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:04,630
Never wanted factory work.

128
00:07:04,630 --> 00:07:05,480
No need to bother.

129
00:07:05,920 --> 00:07:07,070
Then that's the second type.

130
00:07:07,510 --> 00:07:08,600
Four options

131
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:09,240
for you.

132
00:07:09,390 --> 00:07:10,750
Shop girl, bar girl,

133
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:11,800
waitress, or maid.

134
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:12,630
Experience matters

135
00:07:12,720 --> 00:07:13,800
for waitresses.

136
00:07:13,830 --> 00:07:14,560
Got any?

137
00:07:15,920 --> 00:07:16,560
Probably not.

138
00:07:16,830 --> 00:07:18,040
Can you drink?

139
00:07:22,720 --> 00:07:23,480
Looks like

140
00:07:23,630 --> 00:07:24,510
you're not going

141
00:07:24,600 --> 00:07:25,510
for the bar girl job.

142
00:07:26,830 --> 00:07:27,800
Shop girls

143
00:07:27,870 --> 00:07:29,240
usually have to

144
00:07:29,360 --> 00:07:31,310
dress sexy and bold.

145
00:07:32,160 --> 00:07:32,720
Probably not

146
00:07:32,720 --> 00:07:33,750
your thing either.

147
00:07:34,040 --> 00:07:34,750
That leaves maid.

148
00:07:34,830 --> 00:07:35,800
That means housework,

149
00:07:35,800 --> 00:07:36,950
elderly care, and childcare.

150
00:07:36,950 --> 00:07:37,510
Can you?

151
00:07:37,950 --> 00:07:39,040
Even if you're hired,

152
00:07:39,040 --> 00:07:39,600
the wife

153
00:07:39,600 --> 00:07:40,720
wouldn't trust a pretty maid.

154
00:07:40,720 --> 00:07:42,560
Shut up! Don't follow me!

155
00:07:42,830 --> 00:07:43,190
Wait.

156
00:07:43,190 --> 00:07:44,040
Let me finish.

157
00:07:44,390 --> 00:07:45,120
Last few words.

158
00:07:45,240 --> 00:07:46,070
Last few words.

159
00:07:46,870 --> 00:07:47,430
Honestly,

160
00:07:47,510 --> 00:07:48,750
I'm really trying

161
00:07:48,830 --> 00:07:49,630
to help.

162
00:07:50,190 --> 00:07:51,240
On April 25th this year,

163
00:07:51,360 --> 00:07:53,120
Shenzhen announced plans

164
00:07:53,160 --> 00:07:54,120
for high-tech businesses.

165
00:07:54,240 --> 00:07:54,870
They're courting

166
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:56,360
college grads

167
00:07:56,430 --> 00:07:58,120
from all over the country,

168
00:07:58,190 --> 00:07:59,070
especially in tech.

169
00:07:59,510 --> 00:08:00,120
Think about it.

170
00:08:00,240 --> 00:08:02,070
Under this tendency, how do you make it

171
00:08:02,160 --> 00:08:03,480
without a degree?

172
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:05,120
You're obsessed with degrees!

173
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:06,600
To make a commission,

174
00:08:06,680 --> 00:08:08,240
you dismiss what low-educated workers

175
00:08:08,360 --> 00:08:09,630
contribute to this city.

176
00:08:10,950 --> 00:08:11,390
Look at

177
00:08:11,480 --> 00:08:12,870
that cleaner.

178
00:08:15,830 --> 00:08:16,390
And him.

179
00:08:16,630 --> 00:08:17,600
He's washing cars.

180
00:08:18,190 --> 00:08:18,600
There.

181
00:08:18,830 --> 00:08:19,870
A cook delivering food.

182
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:21,680
Don't they contribute

183
00:08:21,720 --> 00:08:22,430
to this city?

184
00:08:23,310 --> 00:08:24,360
Narrow-minded people

185
00:08:24,430 --> 00:08:25,430
can be teachers now?

186
00:08:26,190 --> 00:08:28,160
Just a swindler and a snob.

187
00:08:28,720 --> 00:08:30,000
You're crossing the line.

188
00:08:30,560 --> 00:08:31,600
But your logic

189
00:08:31,630 --> 00:08:32,360
is pretty sharp.

190
00:08:32,510 --> 00:08:33,030
Speak well too.

191
00:08:33,030 --> 00:08:34,030
Stop, or I'll call the cops.

192
00:08:35,150 --> 00:08:36,270
Are you blind?

193
00:08:37,240 --> 00:08:38,120
I'm sorry!

194
00:08:40,360 --> 00:08:41,000
It didn't spill.

195
00:08:41,270 --> 00:08:42,270
It did spill!

196
00:08:42,270 --> 00:08:43,200
And you say it didn't?

197
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:44,720
How can they eat this now?

198
00:08:47,320 --> 00:08:48,080
I'll pay you.

199
00:08:49,320 --> 00:08:50,390
Already late from traffic,

200
00:08:50,390 --> 00:08:51,200
and now you.

201
00:08:51,440 --> 00:08:51,960
Sorry.

202
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:53,510
Why do I have such bad luck?

203
00:08:57,670 --> 00:08:58,720
Why are you following me?

204
00:08:59,120 --> 00:08:59,960
How much is it?

205
00:09:00,030 --> 00:09:00,790
Just tell me.

206
00:09:01,550 --> 00:09:02,910
I'm not petty.

207
00:09:02,910 --> 00:09:03,870
Don't need a girl to pay.

208
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:04,670
Don't follow me!

209
00:09:05,120 --> 00:09:06,150
Sir, wait.

210
00:09:06,240 --> 00:09:06,870
Mr. Hu,

211
00:09:07,120 --> 00:09:07,840
I'm late.

212
00:09:08,510 --> 00:09:08,960
You're here.

213
00:09:09,200 --> 00:09:10,910
The soup spilled.

214
00:09:11,510 --> 00:09:13,080
I'm really sorry.

215
00:09:13,870 --> 00:09:14,960
I'll add an extra dish tonight.

216
00:09:15,320 --> 00:09:15,840
It's fine.

217
00:09:16,120 --> 00:09:17,320
Just a quick bite is enough.

218
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:18,870
You guys

219
00:09:19,030 --> 00:09:20,200
cook for hundreds

220
00:09:20,510 --> 00:09:22,000
and handle delivery.

221
00:09:22,390 --> 00:09:23,080
That's tough.

222
00:09:26,910 --> 00:09:27,630
Zhu.

223
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:30,550
No one educated

224
00:09:30,910 --> 00:09:32,320
in your cafeteria?

225
00:09:34,200 --> 00:09:35,320
See for yourself.

226
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:36,600
What is it?

227
00:09:40,960 --> 00:09:41,750
Mo shu pork.

228
00:09:43,150 --> 00:09:44,320
Zucchini and eggs.

229
00:09:46,670 --> 00:09:47,200
See?

230
00:09:47,790 --> 00:09:48,720
Someone's laughing.

231
00:09:49,910 --> 00:09:50,720
The people here

232
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:51,960
are all educated.

233
00:09:52,390 --> 00:09:53,320
With writing like this,

234
00:09:54,080 --> 00:09:55,150
you wanna embarrass

235
00:09:55,150 --> 00:09:55,960
the company?

236
00:09:58,240 --> 00:09:58,720
Well,

237
00:09:59,550 --> 00:10:00,320
I'll find

238
00:10:00,440 --> 00:10:01,480
an educated person

239
00:10:02,080 --> 00:10:03,000
for your cafeteria.

240
00:10:04,910 --> 00:10:05,390
Sir,

241
00:10:05,670 --> 00:10:06,550
here's my resume.

242
00:10:06,670 --> 00:10:07,600
See if I qualify.

243
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:12,960
Nice handwriting.

244
00:10:13,440 --> 00:10:13,960
Thanks.

245
00:10:15,600 --> 00:10:17,120
I have some college, no degree.

246
00:10:19,390 --> 00:10:20,550
Why didn't you

247
00:10:20,750 --> 00:10:21,630
finish college?

248
00:10:22,510 --> 00:10:23,360
Family difficulties?

249
00:10:23,630 --> 00:10:24,510
Your outfit

250
00:10:24,550 --> 00:10:25,510
says otherwise.

251
00:10:26,150 --> 00:10:26,910
Actually,

252
00:10:27,150 --> 00:10:28,600
I was just joking.

253
00:10:28,960 --> 00:10:30,600
The work site is tough.

254
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:31,870
A college girl

255
00:10:32,390 --> 00:10:33,550
working in a cafeteria?

256
00:10:34,120 --> 00:10:35,200
That's beneath you.

257
00:10:35,790 --> 00:10:36,550
I want to.

258
00:10:37,360 --> 00:10:37,960
I... though I

259
00:10:37,960 --> 00:10:38,910
have no experience,

260
00:10:39,080 --> 00:10:40,630
I'm a hard worker and a quick learner.

261
00:10:40,630 --> 00:10:41,480
I can take the exhaustion.

262
00:10:41,550 --> 00:10:42,080
I promise

263
00:10:42,240 --> 00:10:42,790
no more typos

264
00:10:42,840 --> 00:10:44,000
on the menu.

265
00:10:46,240 --> 00:10:46,790
Zhang,

266
00:10:47,080 --> 00:10:48,270
why not hire her?

267
00:10:48,910 --> 00:10:49,440
Fine.

268
00:10:50,030 --> 00:10:51,240
We need people anyway.

269
00:10:51,720 --> 00:10:53,080
She seems sharp.

270
00:10:53,790 --> 00:10:54,240
Hire her.

271
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:56,550
Zhu,

272
00:10:57,240 --> 00:10:58,000
bring her along.

273
00:10:58,600 --> 00:10:59,960
Your dad runs the cafeteria.

274
00:11:00,510 --> 00:11:01,320
As for the contract,

275
00:11:01,600 --> 00:11:02,910
let your dad take...

276
00:11:03,630 --> 00:11:04,320
Fang Wanzhi.

277
00:11:04,510 --> 00:11:04,960
Fang.

278
00:11:05,320 --> 00:11:05,870
Take Fang

279
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:07,240
to Personnel.

280
00:11:07,600 --> 00:11:08,510
Thanks, sir.

281
00:11:09,200 --> 00:11:10,080
Thank you.

282
00:11:11,510 --> 00:11:12,670
Academy of Continuing Education.

283
00:11:12,840 --> 00:11:14,030
Your ticket to the job market.

284
00:11:15,080 --> 00:11:16,000
Take a look.

285
00:11:16,360 --> 00:11:17,360
Continuing Education.

286
00:11:18,510 --> 00:11:19,750
Your ticket to the job market.

287
00:11:21,600 --> 00:11:22,240
Some bad news

288
00:11:22,270 --> 00:11:23,320
for you.

289
00:11:23,720 --> 00:11:25,270
I found a job.

290
00:11:29,240 --> 00:11:29,910
Congratulations.

291
00:11:30,240 --> 00:11:31,360
How about

292
00:11:31,360 --> 00:11:32,080
night school?

293
00:11:32,270 --> 00:11:32,960
Pass the exams,

294
00:11:33,030 --> 00:11:33,550
clock the hours,

295
00:11:33,670 --> 00:11:34,630
and the diploma's yours.

296
00:11:35,080 --> 00:11:35,480
Here.

297
00:11:36,270 --> 00:11:37,150
Hope I'll never

298
00:11:37,270 --> 00:11:38,270
see you again.

299
00:11:39,390 --> 00:11:39,960
Let's go.

300
00:11:41,030 --> 00:11:41,480
I'll take it.

301
00:11:42,200 --> 00:11:42,720
Thanks.

302
00:11:43,510 --> 00:11:44,240
Fang Wanzhi!

303
00:11:44,790 --> 00:11:45,600
I'm Gao Xiang!

304
00:11:45,720 --> 00:11:47,240
Come see me when you want!

305
00:11:47,600 --> 00:11:48,720
I'll save you a spot

306
00:11:48,720 --> 00:11:49,550
with a discount!

307
00:11:52,270 --> 00:11:52,910
That car.

308
00:12:14,390 --> 00:12:14,910
We're here.

309
00:12:15,510 --> 00:12:16,080
Get out.

310
00:12:20,670 --> 00:12:21,080
Thanks.

311
00:12:21,080 --> 00:12:21,440
Here.

312
00:12:26,320 --> 00:12:26,750
Dad,

313
00:12:27,270 --> 00:12:28,000
Mr. Hu

314
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:28,720
hired a girl.

315
00:12:28,840 --> 00:12:29,270
She's here.

316
00:12:46,270 --> 00:12:49,240
Doesn't look like a worker.

317
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:03,630
He's my dad.

318
00:13:04,270 --> 00:13:04,910
Hello.

319
00:13:05,270 --> 00:13:06,480
Do you have a brush pen?

320
00:13:09,870 --> 00:13:11,240
Heard you can write.

321
00:13:11,960 --> 00:13:12,840
No need to show off.

322
00:13:13,150 --> 00:13:13,750
From now on,

323
00:13:13,910 --> 00:13:15,630
you write the menu.

324
00:13:16,080 --> 00:13:17,030
Use chalk.

325
00:13:18,480 --> 00:13:19,790
There's a typo.

326
00:13:22,480 --> 00:13:23,320
I wrote that.

327
00:13:24,200 --> 00:13:26,120
Which... which one is wrong?

328
00:13:28,080 --> 00:13:30,240
It does look a bit off.

329
00:13:30,960 --> 00:13:31,910
Uneducated kid!

330
00:13:32,480 --> 00:13:33,720
If you'd studied hard,

331
00:13:34,390 --> 00:13:35,670
we wouldn't embarrass ourselves!

332
00:13:37,270 --> 00:13:38,390
You wrote that?

333
00:13:39,270 --> 00:13:40,960
Maybe I remembered wrong.

334
00:13:41,790 --> 00:13:43,510
I think

335
00:13:44,240 --> 00:13:48,120
the correct spelling of "waste" is w-a-s-t-e.

336
00:13:48,790 --> 00:13:50,360
This one looks right.

337
00:13:51,120 --> 00:13:52,270
But you wrote w-a-s-t.

338
00:13:52,630 --> 00:13:53,630
You're a waste!

339
00:13:58,320 --> 00:13:59,150
I spelled it wrong.

340
00:13:59,910 --> 00:14:00,790
You caught me.

341
00:14:01,240 --> 00:14:02,440
Don't say that.

342
00:14:02,790 --> 00:14:04,080
At the job fair,

343
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:05,270
they said

344
00:14:05,600 --> 00:14:07,200
you cook for hundreds.

345
00:14:07,320 --> 00:14:08,240
You must be busy.

346
00:14:08,510 --> 00:14:10,200
You probably rushed

347
00:14:10,440 --> 00:14:11,150
and messed up.

348
00:14:13,510 --> 00:14:14,150
Rushed?

349
00:14:14,960 --> 00:14:15,480
Zhu,

350
00:14:16,480 --> 00:14:17,120
you should

351
00:14:17,480 --> 00:14:18,840
learn from Fang.

352
00:14:19,630 --> 00:14:20,910
See how she talks.

353
00:14:21,320 --> 00:14:22,840
Now that's a college student.

354
00:14:45,670 --> 00:14:46,480
It's not great.

355
00:14:46,600 --> 00:14:47,870
Will this do?

356
00:14:49,790 --> 00:14:50,440
Not great?

357
00:14:51,750 --> 00:14:53,000
This is calligraphy!

358
00:14:53,630 --> 00:14:54,240
I'm impressed.

359
00:14:55,240 --> 00:14:56,270
No wonder

360
00:14:56,750 --> 00:14:57,670
Mr. Hu hired you.

361
00:14:58,750 --> 00:14:59,240
Alright.

362
00:14:59,910 --> 00:15:00,840
Come sign

363
00:15:01,480 --> 00:15:02,030
the contract.

364
00:15:02,840 --> 00:15:03,440
Thank you.

365
00:15:03,840 --> 00:15:05,000
No need

366
00:15:05,200 --> 00:15:05,790
for formality.

367
00:15:06,720 --> 00:15:08,320
Just call me Liu.

368
00:15:09,150 --> 00:15:09,750
Liu.

369
00:15:10,790 --> 00:15:11,630
The salary is 1,100 yuan.

370
00:15:11,750 --> 00:15:12,630
Plus allowances.

371
00:15:12,750 --> 00:15:14,480
You can get 1,240.

372
00:15:17,440 --> 00:15:18,150
Not happy?

373
00:15:19,150 --> 00:15:20,480
Wages here...

374
00:15:20,750 --> 00:15:21,320
Well,

375
00:15:21,870 --> 00:15:23,720
it's not high for Shenzhen.

376
00:15:24,120 --> 00:15:25,390
But you're a beginner...

377
00:15:25,480 --> 00:15:26,550
That's not what I meant.

378
00:15:26,790 --> 00:15:28,320
I mean, wages here

379
00:15:28,390 --> 00:15:29,550
are way higher than inland.

380
00:15:30,270 --> 00:15:31,320
Yet the work's harder.

381
00:15:31,550 --> 00:15:32,790
We don't carry slackers.

382
00:15:33,440 --> 00:15:34,390
If you're not sure,

383
00:15:34,550 --> 00:15:35,630
start with probation.

384
00:15:36,200 --> 00:15:37,270
Then you can get paid

385
00:15:37,440 --> 00:15:38,360
by the day.

386
00:15:38,600 --> 00:15:39,270
Otherwise,

387
00:15:39,550 --> 00:15:40,440
no full month,

388
00:15:41,080 --> 00:15:41,870
no pay.

389
00:15:42,270 --> 00:15:43,270
No need for probation.

390
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:44,630
Then sign

391
00:15:44,750 --> 00:15:45,750
this labor contract.

392
00:15:46,750 --> 00:15:47,550
Till Spring Festival.

393
00:16:13,550 --> 00:16:14,120
This is

394
00:16:14,360 --> 00:16:14,870
the dorm.

395
00:16:16,720 --> 00:16:18,670
The leaders care about
the female workers,

396
00:16:18,790 --> 00:16:19,440
so they built it.

397
00:16:20,030 --> 00:16:20,910
Even got water up there.

398
00:16:21,440 --> 00:16:22,200
Took a lot of work.

399
00:16:23,630 --> 00:16:25,120
Liu Zhu and I live there.

400
00:16:25,480 --> 00:16:26,910
Call me if you need anything.

401
00:16:28,670 --> 00:16:29,480
Need help

402
00:16:29,840 --> 00:16:31,270
with your luggage?

403
00:16:31,720 --> 00:16:33,120
No thanks. I can handle it.

404
00:16:44,720 --> 00:16:45,870
Come to the kitchen

405
00:16:46,240 --> 00:16:47,480
when you're done.

406
00:17:42,640 --> 00:17:43,310
Who are you?

407
00:17:43,920 --> 00:17:45,240
Hi, I'm new here.

408
00:17:45,310 --> 00:17:46,680
I don't care who you are.

409
00:17:47,160 --> 00:17:47,920
Who let you in?

410
00:17:48,240 --> 00:17:48,880
Go out!

411
00:17:49,510 --> 00:17:50,400
What are you doing?

412
00:17:50,550 --> 00:17:51,240
Two girls in here

413
00:17:51,240 --> 00:17:52,000
are bad enough.

414
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:53,240
And now three?

415
00:17:53,790 --> 00:17:55,350
Go out. Now!

416
00:17:55,550 --> 00:17:57,160
How can you do this?

417
00:17:58,640 --> 00:17:59,750
I was just hired.

418
00:17:59,880 --> 00:18:01,200
Liu told me to live here.

419
00:18:01,310 --> 00:18:02,750
That doesn't matter.

420
00:18:02,920 --> 00:18:03,920
I don't agree!

421
00:18:09,480 --> 00:18:10,720
Open the door!

422
00:18:27,110 --> 00:18:27,720
Hey!

423
00:18:28,440 --> 00:18:29,480
You won't let me in?

424
00:18:30,200 --> 00:18:31,200
Then don't blame me

425
00:18:31,270 --> 00:18:32,350
if you can't get out.

426
00:18:32,920 --> 00:18:34,070
(I also have a key.)

427
00:18:39,550 --> 00:18:40,680
New girl, open up!

428
00:18:41,310 --> 00:18:42,480
Let's just calm down.

429
00:18:43,200 --> 00:18:44,830
(Calm down? No!)

430
00:18:47,720 --> 00:18:48,590
I'm your new coworker.

431
00:18:48,720 --> 00:18:49,920
Shouldn't you be friendly?

432
00:18:50,310 --> 00:18:51,880
You're mocking me?

433
00:18:52,160 --> 00:18:52,550
I...

434
00:18:54,750 --> 00:18:56,160
You jinx.

435
00:18:57,110 --> 00:18:58,680
Open up. I'll teach you a lesson!

436
00:18:58,790 --> 00:18:59,550
Wanna fight?

437
00:18:59,830 --> 00:19:01,030
I'm out.

438
00:19:01,480 --> 00:19:02,160
Liu told me

439
00:19:02,160 --> 00:19:03,310
to get to the kitchen.

440
00:19:03,590 --> 00:19:04,400
I'm off.

441
00:19:05,830 --> 00:19:06,480
Hey!

442
00:19:06,790 --> 00:19:08,240
I gotta get to the kitchen too.

443
00:19:08,480 --> 00:19:10,440
(Or that old man will dock my pay.)

444
00:19:10,830 --> 00:19:12,310
What can I do?

445
00:19:12,920 --> 00:19:13,920
I was assigned

446
00:19:13,960 --> 00:19:14,790
to this dorm.

447
00:19:14,960 --> 00:19:16,200
We're roommates.

448
00:19:16,440 --> 00:19:17,400
(But you kicked me out)

449
00:19:17,480 --> 00:19:18,640
(and threw my stuff.)

450
00:19:18,830 --> 00:19:19,750
(Even want a fight!)

451
00:19:20,200 --> 00:19:21,110
I wouldn't dare.

452
00:19:23,830 --> 00:19:24,510
Fang Wanzhi?

453
00:19:25,400 --> 00:19:26,270
Why don't you go in?

454
00:19:29,160 --> 00:19:29,880
Juan!

455
00:19:30,200 --> 00:19:31,440
(Help!)

456
00:19:31,550 --> 00:19:32,160
(This new girl)

457
00:19:32,200 --> 00:19:33,720
(locked me in.)

458
00:19:34,030 --> 00:19:35,640
(I'm gonna teach her a lesson!)

459
00:19:40,510 --> 00:19:41,240
What's going on?

460
00:19:53,270 --> 00:19:54,720
Look at the time.

461
00:19:56,440 --> 00:19:57,000
All three

462
00:19:57,030 --> 00:19:58,160
still haven't shown up.

463
00:19:59,160 --> 00:20:00,200
Getting anxious?

464
00:20:01,030 --> 00:20:01,720
Keep kneading!

465
00:20:08,240 --> 00:20:09,510
Juan, let's show her.

466
00:20:09,510 --> 00:20:11,030
How domineering.

467
00:20:11,200 --> 00:20:12,440
You threw her out?

468
00:20:15,160 --> 00:20:16,400
She played the victim?

469
00:20:16,640 --> 00:20:18,070
I know you so well.

470
00:20:18,200 --> 00:20:18,590
What?

471
00:20:18,640 --> 00:20:19,680
Wanna fight her?

472
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:23,550
We're the only girls on the site.

473
00:20:23,550 --> 00:20:24,960
You trying to embarrass us?

474
00:20:27,640 --> 00:20:28,350
I'm Li Juan.

475
00:20:28,750 --> 00:20:29,550
She's Hao Qianqian.

476
00:20:31,400 --> 00:20:32,110
How old are you?

477
00:20:33,350 --> 00:20:34,030
Twenty-one.

478
00:20:34,350 --> 00:20:34,920
Gosh!

479
00:20:35,030 --> 00:20:35,960
You're the youngest.

480
00:20:36,200 --> 00:20:37,240
Hao Qianqian's the eldest,

481
00:20:37,270 --> 00:20:38,270
yet doesn't care about anyone.

482
00:20:39,880 --> 00:20:41,030
Who's ever cared about me?

483
00:20:41,510 --> 00:20:42,200
This is too small

484
00:20:42,270 --> 00:20:43,310
for three people.

485
00:20:43,480 --> 00:20:45,640
This container is large enough!

486
00:20:45,880 --> 00:20:46,920
When I worked in Guangzhou,

487
00:20:47,030 --> 00:20:47,750
a place this size

488
00:20:47,790 --> 00:20:49,030
would hold ten people.

489
00:20:49,350 --> 00:20:50,640
Well, I think it's small.

490
00:20:51,160 --> 00:20:52,160
You're a nice person?

491
00:20:52,790 --> 00:20:53,510
Then you two

492
00:20:53,510 --> 00:20:54,550
share one bed.

493
00:20:55,400 --> 00:20:57,550
Who said anything about sharing a bed?

494
00:20:57,640 --> 00:20:58,830
The manager arranged it.

495
00:20:58,880 --> 00:21:00,070
I just went to get bedding,

496
00:21:00,160 --> 00:21:01,270
and you threw a fit?

497
00:21:01,640 --> 00:21:02,110
(Li Juan!)

498
00:21:04,030 --> 00:21:04,550
Hi!

499
00:21:05,160 --> 00:21:05,720
Bed's here.

500
00:21:06,160 --> 00:21:06,830
Where to put it?

501
00:21:07,510 --> 00:21:08,400
The two inside

502
00:21:08,720 --> 00:21:10,400
go against the wall.

503
00:21:10,480 --> 00:21:11,590
This one goes by the window.

504
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:12,400
Okay.

505
00:21:13,750 --> 00:21:15,110
How come she gets the window spot?

506
00:21:15,440 --> 00:21:16,030
Enough!

507
00:21:17,110 --> 00:21:18,310
We're all struggling out here.

508
00:21:18,310 --> 00:21:19,440
What's your problem?

509
00:21:27,160 --> 00:21:27,790
Qian,

510
00:21:28,720 --> 00:21:29,720
it was a misunderstanding.

511
00:21:30,440 --> 00:21:31,750
My attitude was bad too.

512
00:21:32,400 --> 00:21:33,400
Please don't mind it.

513
00:21:38,030 --> 00:21:39,590
You changed your tune so fast.

514
00:21:40,160 --> 00:21:41,640
See, Juan?

515
00:21:41,790 --> 00:21:43,110
Watch out for her kind.

516
00:21:43,310 --> 00:21:44,110
Come on.

517
00:21:44,480 --> 00:21:45,510
That's just how she is.

518
00:21:45,830 --> 00:21:46,750
Don't put up with her

519
00:21:46,790 --> 00:21:47,400
or suck up to her.

520
00:21:47,510 --> 00:21:48,640
Just ignore her.

521
00:21:49,070 --> 00:21:50,110
Like you ever

522
00:21:50,160 --> 00:21:51,070
did that!

523
00:22:10,310 --> 00:22:11,350
Oh my god!

524
00:22:11,510 --> 00:22:12,680
This won't work.

525
00:22:12,830 --> 00:22:14,070
We're not cooking for two.

526
00:22:14,200 --> 00:22:15,310
It's over 200.

527
00:22:15,880 --> 00:22:16,240
Well,

528
00:22:16,960 --> 00:22:17,510
I'll teach you.

529
00:22:23,640 --> 00:22:24,640
See? Like this.

530
00:22:24,880 --> 00:22:26,000
Just rinse it a few times.

531
00:22:26,590 --> 00:22:28,070
Isn't that wasteful?

532
00:22:28,480 --> 00:22:29,880
Leeks are cheap.

533
00:22:29,960 --> 00:22:30,960
Shenzhen labor

534
00:22:31,160 --> 00:22:32,880
costs more.

535
00:22:33,240 --> 00:22:33,640
Besides,

536
00:22:33,790 --> 00:22:34,830
if you're that meticulous,

537
00:22:34,960 --> 00:22:36,270
dinner's gonna be late.

538
00:22:36,640 --> 00:22:38,000
Getting the workers fed on time

539
00:22:38,160 --> 00:22:39,070
is what matters.

540
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:40,480
By the way,

541
00:22:41,110 --> 00:22:41,790
these won't

542
00:22:42,440 --> 00:22:44,400
go to waste.

543
00:22:44,720 --> 00:22:45,590
After dinner,

544
00:22:45,720 --> 00:22:46,720
clean them up

545
00:22:46,830 --> 00:22:47,350
and pickle them.

546
00:22:47,640 --> 00:22:48,790
Tomorrow, mix them with chili,

547
00:22:48,920 --> 00:22:49,720
and they're pickles.

548
00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:50,750
My invention.

549
00:22:50,920 --> 00:22:52,070
They all love it.

550
00:22:52,440 --> 00:22:53,030
Got it?

551
00:22:53,310 --> 00:22:53,960
Got it.

552
00:22:54,270 --> 00:22:54,720
Go on.

553
00:22:57,750 --> 00:22:58,680
Be careful.

554
00:22:58,790 --> 00:22:59,680
Don't cut your fingers.

555
00:22:59,830 --> 00:23:00,400
Yeah.

556
00:23:11,830 --> 00:23:13,110
No rush.

557
00:23:13,110 --> 00:23:14,590
You'll learn in a few days.

558
00:23:16,590 --> 00:23:17,920
Juan, you're so nice.

559
00:23:18,720 --> 00:23:19,640
Huh?

560
00:23:19,790 --> 00:23:21,200
I'm just a dumb

561
00:23:21,240 --> 00:23:21,960
and blunt girl.

562
00:23:22,030 --> 00:23:23,160
Maybe I'll say something

563
00:23:23,270 --> 00:23:24,310
that hurts you.

564
00:23:24,440 --> 00:23:25,920
Hope you won't mind.

565
00:23:26,240 --> 00:23:27,960
It's never personal.

566
00:23:31,750 --> 00:23:32,920
Where's she from?

567
00:23:34,030 --> 00:23:34,830
I don't know.

568
00:23:35,590 --> 00:23:36,790
Today she's from Sichuan.

569
00:23:37,000 --> 00:23:38,310
Tomorrow, Zhejiang.

570
00:23:38,960 --> 00:23:40,110
Yesterday, raised by grandparents

571
00:23:40,240 --> 00:23:41,110
in the countryside.

572
00:23:41,270 --> 00:23:42,400
Tomorrow, living it up with them

573
00:23:42,510 --> 00:23:43,440
in the city.

574
00:23:43,680 --> 00:23:44,790
Who knows what's true?

575
00:23:49,830 --> 00:23:50,830
If you're so tough,

576
00:23:50,880 --> 00:23:51,400
break the basin.

577
00:23:52,680 --> 00:23:53,510
We live together,

578
00:23:53,550 --> 00:23:55,030
and we are close.

579
00:23:55,830 --> 00:23:57,400
Why so chummy with her?

580
00:23:57,640 --> 00:23:59,030
Can't you tell

581
00:23:59,110 --> 00:23:59,920
it's her first job?

582
00:24:00,070 --> 00:24:01,110
And you even bully her.

583
00:24:01,720 --> 00:24:03,240
Have some sympathy, okay?

584
00:24:04,680 --> 00:24:06,200
Who sympathizes with me?

585
00:24:41,270 --> 00:24:41,680
Here.

586
00:24:41,920 --> 00:24:42,640
Some cucumber?

587
00:24:43,640 --> 00:24:44,400
Have some meat.

588
00:24:44,480 --> 00:24:44,880
Okay.

589
00:24:47,830 --> 00:24:48,550
Wanna cabbage?

590
00:24:51,640 --> 00:24:52,720
Everyone, look at our menu.

591
00:24:52,830 --> 00:24:53,790
Good, right?

592
00:24:53,960 --> 00:24:56,110
We've got a new college girl!

593
00:24:57,160 --> 00:24:58,440
The new girl? So pretty!

594
00:24:58,590 --> 00:24:59,160
We'll

595
00:24:59,350 --> 00:25:00,880
all eat here from now on.

596
00:25:01,270 --> 00:25:02,070
These three girls

597
00:25:02,350 --> 00:25:03,400
are all gorgeous.

598
00:25:04,350 --> 00:25:05,070
Come on!

599
00:25:05,310 --> 00:25:06,310
They're average.

600
00:25:06,510 --> 00:25:07,480
None of them

601
00:25:07,510 --> 00:25:08,510
hold a candle to my wife.

602
00:25:13,880 --> 00:25:15,720
Actually, they're kind.

603
00:25:16,480 --> 00:25:17,550
Work's tough here.

604
00:25:17,680 --> 00:25:18,590
And few women here.

605
00:25:19,070 --> 00:25:20,070
So at meals,

606
00:25:20,240 --> 00:25:21,030
they steal glances

607
00:25:21,240 --> 00:25:21,960
and murmur.

608
00:25:22,400 --> 00:25:23,400
Don't take it to heart.

609
00:25:24,480 --> 00:25:25,160
I don't.

610
00:25:37,000 --> 00:25:37,510
Take a break.

611
00:25:37,640 --> 00:25:38,110
Eat something.

612
00:25:38,200 --> 00:25:38,960
I got you a plate.

613
00:25:39,960 --> 00:25:40,830
I have no appetite.

614
00:25:42,000 --> 00:25:43,240
If I could,

615
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:45,440
I'd go lie down.

616
00:25:46,440 --> 00:25:47,240
You go back then.

617
00:25:47,640 --> 00:25:48,310
Don't come back.

618
00:25:48,640 --> 00:25:49,240
I will

619
00:25:49,240 --> 00:25:50,030
wrap this up.

620
00:25:50,590 --> 00:25:51,790
That would be inappropriate.

621
00:25:53,200 --> 00:25:54,550
Just half an hour.

622
00:25:55,030 --> 00:25:55,510
Go.

623
00:25:56,110 --> 00:25:56,720
Thank you.

624
00:25:59,160 --> 00:26:00,070
Hold on, Fang.

625
00:26:01,070 --> 00:26:01,550
Stop

626
00:26:02,030 --> 00:26:02,960
what you're doing.

627
00:26:03,640 --> 00:26:04,350
Meeting time.

628
00:26:05,640 --> 00:26:06,440
Just now,

629
00:26:06,720 --> 00:26:08,790
Mr. Hu

630
00:26:09,030 --> 00:26:09,790
told me

631
00:26:10,720 --> 00:26:11,480
our cafeteria

632
00:26:12,400 --> 00:26:14,000
ranked number one

633
00:26:14,680 --> 00:26:15,400
last month.

634
00:26:15,590 --> 00:26:16,790
Wonderful!

635
00:26:19,880 --> 00:26:20,440
Wanzhi,

636
00:26:21,070 --> 00:26:21,720
there are

637
00:26:21,750 --> 00:26:22,790
four cafeterias.

638
00:26:23,030 --> 00:26:24,590
Every month, the workers vote

639
00:26:24,720 --> 00:26:25,790
for the best one.

640
00:26:27,000 --> 00:26:27,880
Our food

641
00:26:28,480 --> 00:26:30,030
is clean and tasty.

642
00:26:30,920 --> 00:26:32,830
Everyone wants to eat here.

643
00:26:33,830 --> 00:26:36,270
So Mr. Hu

644
00:26:36,830 --> 00:26:37,790
wants us

645
00:26:38,240 --> 00:26:39,510
to take on a bit more.

646
00:26:39,750 --> 00:26:40,350
More workers

647
00:26:40,510 --> 00:26:41,640
are gonna eat here?

648
00:26:42,200 --> 00:26:43,400
We're swamped.

649
00:26:43,400 --> 00:26:44,880
Can't handle more!

650
00:26:46,000 --> 00:26:47,240
We cook

651
00:26:47,310 --> 00:26:48,000
for 260.

652
00:26:48,640 --> 00:26:50,070
Then we can cook

653
00:26:50,270 --> 00:26:50,880
for 330.

654
00:26:51,200 --> 00:26:52,030
What?

655
00:26:52,350 --> 00:26:53,510
Add 70 more people?

656
00:26:53,680 --> 00:26:54,960
There are only four of us!

657
00:26:56,160 --> 00:26:57,310
No, five.

658
00:26:58,240 --> 00:26:59,070
Her? Useless.

659
00:26:59,070 --> 00:26:59,750
Her being here

660
00:26:59,790 --> 00:27:00,510
changes nothing.

661
00:27:01,030 --> 00:27:02,110
What's wrong with her?

662
00:27:02,440 --> 00:27:03,310
I think she's good.

663
00:27:03,720 --> 00:27:04,750
Better than you were.

664
00:27:05,920 --> 00:27:06,510
What?

665
00:27:06,680 --> 00:27:07,240
Enough.

666
00:27:10,880 --> 00:27:11,790
It's true.

667
00:27:12,640 --> 00:27:13,720
At first,

668
00:27:14,070 --> 00:27:15,070
I didn't agree.

669
00:27:15,750 --> 00:27:17,680
Back home,

670
00:27:18,720 --> 00:27:19,830
I had 18

671
00:27:19,920 --> 00:27:21,480
in my kitchen crew,

672
00:27:22,200 --> 00:27:24,270
and we only cooked for 300.

673
00:27:25,070 --> 00:27:26,350
However, Mr. Hu said

674
00:27:27,640 --> 00:27:29,110
if we cook

675
00:27:29,270 --> 00:27:30,440
for 70 more workers,

676
00:27:30,440 --> 00:27:31,350
he will

677
00:27:32,640 --> 00:27:33,590
give us bonuses

678
00:27:34,550 --> 00:27:35,590
at year's end.

679
00:27:37,110 --> 00:27:38,000
Bonuses?

680
00:27:38,000 --> 00:27:38,680
How much?

681
00:27:39,310 --> 00:27:41,070
Fifty percent of our salary.

682
00:27:41,350 --> 00:27:43,000
Paid out at year's end.

683
00:27:43,240 --> 00:27:45,400
Called a year-end bonus.

684
00:27:45,640 --> 00:27:48,000
A year-end bonus? Never heard of it.

685
00:27:48,350 --> 00:27:49,070
Well,

686
00:27:49,240 --> 00:27:50,160
Mr. Hu

687
00:27:50,270 --> 00:27:51,510
is not forcing us

688
00:27:52,070 --> 00:27:53,030
to take it on.

689
00:27:53,440 --> 00:27:55,270
He's just asking us.

690
00:27:55,750 --> 00:27:57,830
If you think it would be tiring,

691
00:27:58,510 --> 00:27:59,350
we can say no.

692
00:27:59,790 --> 00:28:01,270
No, we can handle it.

693
00:28:01,480 --> 00:28:02,750
I've worked so long.

694
00:28:02,960 --> 00:28:03,830
Never gotten

695
00:28:03,920 --> 00:28:04,680
a year-end bonus.

696
00:28:04,880 --> 00:28:06,400
Yeah, I'm all for it.

697
00:28:06,550 --> 00:28:08,000
Besides, it's not that much harder.

698
00:28:08,160 --> 00:28:09,270
We've got an extra person.

699
00:28:09,510 --> 00:28:10,240
Exactly.

700
00:28:12,200 --> 00:28:13,680
Fang, you...

701
00:28:14,270 --> 00:28:16,000
I'm afraid I'll mess up

702
00:28:16,110 --> 00:28:17,000
and drag you down.

703
00:28:17,240 --> 00:28:17,960
Don't worry.

704
00:28:18,350 --> 00:28:19,270
I wasn't kidding.

705
00:28:19,440 --> 00:28:20,240
You are better

706
00:28:20,310 --> 00:28:21,240
than Hao Qianqian was.

707
00:28:23,000 --> 00:28:23,510
Fang,

708
00:28:24,160 --> 00:28:24,880
you're a godsend.

709
00:28:25,400 --> 00:28:25,960
You brought

710
00:28:26,350 --> 00:28:27,400
the cafeteria

711
00:28:27,440 --> 00:28:28,720
such good fortune.

712
00:28:46,830 --> 00:28:47,510
Get up!

713
00:28:48,750 --> 00:28:50,160
What time is it?

714
00:28:50,440 --> 00:28:51,310
Four.

715
00:28:51,400 --> 00:28:52,550
We've got 70 more mouths.

716
00:28:52,680 --> 00:28:53,790
Need to get up earlier.

717
00:28:53,830 --> 00:28:54,350
Hurry!

718
00:28:55,750 --> 00:28:56,480
Come on!

719
00:28:56,750 --> 00:28:57,510
Wanzhi, get up.

720
00:28:59,510 --> 00:29:00,110
Hurry up.

721
00:29:25,510 --> 00:29:26,480
Your blister broke?

722
00:29:28,160 --> 00:29:28,920
How do you know?

723
00:29:29,720 --> 00:29:30,480
Your skin is soft.

724
00:29:30,590 --> 00:29:32,030
It's natural to get hurt.

725
00:29:32,200 --> 00:29:32,590
Well,

726
00:29:33,030 --> 00:29:33,480
come here.

727
00:29:35,680 --> 00:29:36,510
Tape is in my pocket.

728
00:29:36,680 --> 00:29:37,400
Wrap it tight,

729
00:29:37,640 --> 00:29:38,510
and it won't hurt.

730
00:29:42,590 --> 00:29:43,790
I'll finish the work first.

731
00:29:44,160 --> 00:29:44,680
Thank you.

732
00:29:46,680 --> 00:29:47,440
Didn't think

733
00:29:47,480 --> 00:29:48,240
a city kid like you

734
00:29:48,310 --> 00:29:49,400
could be so tough.

735
00:29:55,680 --> 00:29:56,720
I'm not a city kid.

736
00:29:58,830 --> 00:29:59,590
Really?

737
00:29:59,790 --> 00:30:01,000
I'm from the mountains.

738
00:30:01,480 --> 00:30:03,270
The poorest, most isolated village.

739
00:30:04,310 --> 00:30:05,590
Still ten miles

740
00:30:05,640 --> 00:30:06,480
with no road.

741
00:30:07,510 --> 00:30:08,000
What?

742
00:30:09,160 --> 00:30:10,110
Your parents then?

743
00:30:13,110 --> 00:30:13,830
My mom...

744
00:30:16,240 --> 00:30:16,790
passed away.

745
00:30:18,440 --> 00:30:19,110
A long time ago.

746
00:30:20,030 --> 00:30:21,240
My dad...

747
00:30:25,070 --> 00:30:25,960
Even if

748
00:30:26,270 --> 00:30:28,160
you came to settle scores with me,

749
00:30:29,240 --> 00:30:30,030
I don't think

750
00:30:30,070 --> 00:30:31,200
I did anything wrong.

751
00:30:32,030 --> 00:30:33,440
Dad!

752
00:30:33,440 --> 00:30:34,070
Don't call me that!

753
00:30:35,880 --> 00:30:36,920
I don't deserve

754
00:30:38,070 --> 00:30:38,880
that title.

755
00:30:41,830 --> 00:30:43,000
Oh no, let's drop it.

756
00:30:43,510 --> 00:30:44,240
My bad.

757
00:30:46,110 --> 00:30:46,880
Get back to work.

758
00:31:25,070 --> 00:31:26,030
More if you want.

759
00:31:27,920 --> 00:31:29,590
The soymilk is the same on both sides.

760
00:31:29,790 --> 00:31:31,110
You can line up here too.

761
00:31:37,880 --> 00:31:38,750
Why do you want

762
00:31:38,750 --> 00:31:40,000
to line up on her side?

763
00:31:41,160 --> 00:31:41,750
Don't you find

764
00:31:41,750 --> 00:31:42,960
she provides service?

765
00:31:43,480 --> 00:31:44,310
What service?

766
00:31:45,110 --> 00:31:45,830
A smile.

767
00:31:53,790 --> 00:31:54,350
Get lost.

768
00:31:57,270 --> 00:31:57,640
(Juan.)

769
00:31:58,550 --> 00:32:00,480
Know the term

770
00:32:00,480 --> 00:32:01,160
"smiling tiger"?

771
00:32:02,070 --> 00:32:02,640
What's wrong?

772
00:32:03,350 --> 00:32:04,440
That's

773
00:32:04,480 --> 00:32:05,160
Fang Wanzhi.

774
00:32:05,240 --> 00:32:06,400
Be careful around her.

775
00:32:23,400 --> 00:32:24,000
Eat up.

776
00:32:24,790 --> 00:32:25,440
Keep dawdling,

777
00:32:25,920 --> 00:32:27,070
and you'll miss your nap.

778
00:32:28,400 --> 00:32:29,480
I'm not napping anymore.

779
00:32:30,110 --> 00:32:31,240
She's not resting either.

780
00:32:33,070 --> 00:32:33,830
Who?

781
00:32:37,000 --> 00:32:37,550
They.

782
00:32:38,440 --> 00:32:39,830
All of them aren't going back.

783
00:32:40,310 --> 00:32:41,160
Seventy extra people.

784
00:32:41,200 --> 00:32:41,880
They can't handle

785
00:32:42,350 --> 00:32:43,480
the prep work.

786
00:33:08,310 --> 00:33:09,000
Look.

787
00:33:11,110 --> 00:33:12,110
I told you.

788
00:33:12,550 --> 00:33:14,270
He didn't hire her as a helper.

789
00:33:14,510 --> 00:33:16,680
He wants her to be his wife.

790
00:33:23,720 --> 00:33:24,720
Want buns?

791
00:33:25,830 --> 00:33:26,270
Okay.

792
00:33:26,350 --> 00:33:26,880
Here you are.

793
00:33:31,680 --> 00:33:32,350
You too?

794
00:33:32,480 --> 00:33:32,880
Okay.

795
00:33:33,480 --> 00:33:33,880
Enough?

796
00:33:37,160 --> 00:33:37,830
All of these?

797
00:33:39,590 --> 00:33:40,110
Fine.

798
00:33:47,110 --> 00:33:47,680
Get some rest

799
00:33:47,880 --> 00:33:48,920
after you eat.

800
00:33:50,200 --> 00:33:50,960
At 2:30,

801
00:33:51,750 --> 00:33:54,480
Juan and Qian prep with me.

802
00:33:55,400 --> 00:33:56,790
Zhu and Fang

803
00:33:57,070 --> 00:33:58,590
go to buy supplies.

804
00:33:59,240 --> 00:34:01,350
This is how we'll do it from now on.

805
00:34:02,350 --> 00:34:03,110
Why?

806
00:34:09,360 --> 00:34:09,800
Wait...

807
00:34:26,710 --> 00:34:27,800
Is this arrangement

808
00:34:27,800 --> 00:34:28,550
not fair?

809
00:34:31,440 --> 00:34:32,760
Did you know Liu Zhu before?

810
00:34:33,110 --> 00:34:33,670
No.

811
00:34:33,800 --> 00:34:35,190
We met at the job fair.

812
00:34:38,150 --> 00:34:39,030
He's fallen for you.

813
00:34:40,190 --> 00:34:40,670
What?

814
00:34:41,000 --> 00:34:42,320
Liu always wants Liu Zhu

815
00:34:42,400 --> 00:34:43,550
to get married.

816
00:34:44,150 --> 00:34:45,070
You're his target.

817
00:34:46,840 --> 00:34:47,840
Impossible.

818
00:34:48,030 --> 00:34:49,150
Why is it impossible?

819
00:34:49,550 --> 00:34:50,510
The hardest part

820
00:34:50,670 --> 00:34:51,710
is prep.

821
00:34:52,510 --> 00:34:54,110
Buying supplies is easy.

822
00:34:54,280 --> 00:34:55,230
Ride there

823
00:34:55,960 --> 00:34:56,880
and shop around.

824
00:34:57,480 --> 00:34:58,710
He gave this easy work

825
00:34:58,920 --> 00:34:59,920
to you.

826
00:35:00,400 --> 00:35:01,320
That's

827
00:35:01,360 --> 00:35:02,360
for his future

828
00:35:02,440 --> 00:35:03,360
daughter-in-law.

829
00:35:27,360 --> 00:35:28,110
Fang.

830
00:35:29,880 --> 00:35:31,150
Fang.

831
00:35:34,710 --> 00:35:35,190
Fang.

832
00:35:37,320 --> 00:35:38,030
Zhu.

833
00:35:39,960 --> 00:35:40,840
Why not get some sleep

834
00:35:40,920 --> 00:35:41,960
in the dorm?

835
00:35:42,630 --> 00:35:43,710
This is

836
00:35:43,760 --> 00:35:44,800
how I napped at school.

837
00:35:44,840 --> 00:35:45,400
I'm used to it.

838
00:35:47,150 --> 00:35:47,760
Well, let's go.

839
00:35:48,030 --> 00:35:48,760
Grocery shopping.

840
00:35:49,000 --> 00:35:49,920
That market's huge.

841
00:35:50,070 --> 00:35:50,800
It sells everything.

842
00:35:51,360 --> 00:35:51,840
Get in.

843
00:35:52,190 --> 00:35:52,800
Hold on.

844
00:35:55,800 --> 00:35:57,670
My leg's asleep.

845
00:35:59,150 --> 00:35:59,880
Zhu,

846
00:36:00,070 --> 00:36:01,670
we're driving to buy groceries?

847
00:36:02,150 --> 00:36:03,960
It's ten kilometers away.

848
00:36:04,190 --> 00:36:05,880
No car, no way to haul the food.

849
00:36:06,550 --> 00:36:07,710
Then I can't go.

850
00:36:07,840 --> 00:36:08,710
I get carsick.

851
00:36:08,920 --> 00:36:09,880
Really bad.

852
00:36:10,070 --> 00:36:11,800
I'll puke all over your car.

853
00:36:13,630 --> 00:36:14,480
Really?

854
00:36:14,920 --> 00:36:15,880
You were fine

855
00:36:16,070 --> 00:36:16,670
on the ride

856
00:36:16,920 --> 00:36:18,000
back from the job fair.

857
00:36:18,760 --> 00:36:20,030
I took medicine.

858
00:36:20,320 --> 00:36:21,190
The last pill.

859
00:36:21,440 --> 00:36:22,110
Figured I would

860
00:36:22,280 --> 00:36:22,920
be done with cars,

861
00:36:22,960 --> 00:36:24,110
so no extra meds.

862
00:36:24,360 --> 00:36:24,710
Then...

863
00:36:24,960 --> 00:36:25,800
That's good.

864
00:36:25,960 --> 00:36:26,880
Let me go with you.

865
00:36:27,190 --> 00:36:28,360
I'll prep with Juan.

866
00:36:28,550 --> 00:36:28,880
Wait.

867
00:36:29,230 --> 00:36:30,070
What medicine?

868
00:36:30,190 --> 00:36:30,960
I'll buy it.

869
00:36:31,150 --> 00:36:32,550
Can't get that here.

870
00:36:32,760 --> 00:36:33,630
My folks can mail it.

871
00:36:34,480 --> 00:36:34,710
I...

872
00:36:34,710 --> 00:36:36,400
Come on.

873
00:36:36,590 --> 00:36:37,190
Let's go.

874
00:36:37,480 --> 00:36:37,760
Go.

875
00:36:37,760 --> 00:36:39,110
She doesn't want to go with you.

876
00:36:39,110 --> 00:36:40,110
We're out of time.

877
00:36:40,550 --> 00:36:41,230
So annoying!

878
00:36:42,590 --> 00:36:43,280
Get plenty!

879
00:36:51,190 --> 00:36:51,630
Come.

880
00:37:09,800 --> 00:37:11,070
We're back.

881
00:37:22,070 --> 00:37:23,400
Not finished yet?

882
00:37:23,510 --> 00:37:24,280
At this rate,

883
00:37:24,280 --> 00:37:25,280
you'll never finish.

884
00:37:25,960 --> 00:37:27,630
Much slower than me.

885
00:37:28,320 --> 00:37:28,800
We've got

886
00:37:28,920 --> 00:37:30,000
70 more people to feed.

887
00:37:30,150 --> 00:37:31,550
Another word, and I'll kick you.

888
00:37:33,480 --> 00:37:34,000
Quit posing

889
00:37:34,030 --> 00:37:34,880
like a butterfly.

890
00:37:34,880 --> 00:37:35,510
Come help.

891
00:37:35,710 --> 00:37:36,920
You're always scolding me.

892
00:37:38,400 --> 00:37:39,360
Come on!

893
00:37:39,440 --> 00:37:40,000
(Spicy?)

894
00:37:40,000 --> 00:37:41,760
(There's beer tonight!)

895
00:37:41,800 --> 00:37:42,920
(One yuan a bottle!)

896
00:37:43,280 --> 00:37:45,630
Cold beer, one yuan a bottle!

897
00:37:45,920 --> 00:37:46,280
One.

898
00:37:46,440 --> 00:37:47,110
Just one?

899
00:37:47,280 --> 00:37:47,670
Sure.

900
00:37:47,670 --> 00:37:48,190
Okay.

901
00:37:48,480 --> 00:37:48,760
Here.

902
00:37:49,000 --> 00:37:49,630
Fish?

903
00:37:49,840 --> 00:37:50,320
Okay.

904
00:37:50,760 --> 00:37:52,000
Try today's fish.

905
00:37:53,150 --> 00:37:53,960
Here, this.

906
00:37:54,360 --> 00:37:54,960
Spicy?

907
00:37:55,070 --> 00:37:55,510
Yes.

908
00:38:31,400 --> 00:38:32,960
You look so delicate,

909
00:38:34,030 --> 00:38:35,280
but you've got grit.

910
00:39:16,150 --> 00:39:17,000
(Where's Fang Wanzhi?)

911
00:39:17,670 --> 00:39:18,840
She went to the room.

912
00:39:19,710 --> 00:39:20,760
For a college girl,

913
00:39:21,510 --> 00:39:22,960
making it through the day

914
00:39:23,550 --> 00:39:23,960
is hard.

915
00:39:25,630 --> 00:39:26,550
She hasn't eaten yet.

916
00:39:27,000 --> 00:39:27,840
Well, well,

917
00:39:28,550 --> 00:39:29,150
worried?

918
00:39:29,190 --> 00:39:30,000
Then cook something.

919
00:39:30,070 --> 00:39:30,800
I'll deliver it.

920
00:39:51,510 --> 00:39:52,110
Wanzhi.

921
00:39:55,360 --> 00:39:56,000
Fang Wanzhi.

922
00:39:57,070 --> 00:39:57,760
Wake up.

923
00:40:00,150 --> 00:40:00,920
Eat the noodles.

924
00:40:00,920 --> 00:40:01,510
You need

925
00:40:01,510 --> 00:40:02,670
to eat after a long day.

926
00:40:05,360 --> 00:40:06,280
No appetite.

927
00:40:06,630 --> 00:40:07,920
You have to eat.

928
00:40:08,360 --> 00:40:09,710
Or you'll get sick.

929
00:40:09,920 --> 00:40:10,760
Trust me.

930
00:40:12,230 --> 00:40:13,760
Zhu made it for you.

931
00:40:13,880 --> 00:40:14,920
With two eggs.

932
00:40:15,190 --> 00:40:16,190
Get up.

933
00:40:17,440 --> 00:40:17,960
Come on.

934
00:40:24,960 --> 00:40:26,400
You weren't carsick, right?

935
00:40:27,070 --> 00:40:28,630
Didn't want to go alone with Liu Zhu?

936
00:40:29,920 --> 00:40:30,480
Yes...

937
00:40:31,800 --> 00:40:32,630
and no.

938
00:40:33,510 --> 00:40:34,360
What do you mean?

939
00:40:37,320 --> 00:40:38,630
Qian has a problem with me.

940
00:40:39,710 --> 00:40:40,550
(I'm new here.)

941
00:40:40,630 --> 00:40:42,230
(Can't just take all the easy work.)

942
00:40:43,230 --> 00:40:44,550
(So you gave in to her?)

943
00:40:46,030 --> 00:40:46,590
Yes...

944
00:40:46,960 --> 00:40:47,840
and no.

945
00:40:48,550 --> 00:40:49,630
What now?

946
00:40:53,550 --> 00:40:55,400
We three share a room.

947
00:40:56,190 --> 00:40:57,070
If she's mad,

948
00:40:57,190 --> 00:40:58,440
I have to walk on eggshells.

949
00:40:58,670 --> 00:40:59,800
That would be rough on me.

950
00:41:00,550 --> 00:41:01,400
What's more,

951
00:41:01,710 --> 00:41:03,400
though we're not close,

952
00:41:03,760 --> 00:41:04,710
I think

953
00:41:04,920 --> 00:41:05,800
she's probably

954
00:41:05,880 --> 00:41:07,070
had a hard life.

955
00:41:08,320 --> 00:41:09,440
Who's ever cared about me?

956
00:41:10,070 --> 00:41:10,630
Like you ever

957
00:41:10,630 --> 00:41:12,110
did that!

958
00:41:13,110 --> 00:41:13,960
Maybe she

959
00:41:14,710 --> 00:41:15,920
never had anyone

960
00:41:15,920 --> 00:41:16,800
care for her

961
00:41:17,110 --> 00:41:18,670
or show her sympathy.

962
00:41:21,190 --> 00:41:22,760
We're fellow sufferers.

963
00:41:23,110 --> 00:41:24,190
Letting it slide

964
00:41:24,480 --> 00:41:25,000
is nothing.

965
00:41:26,070 --> 00:41:26,670
(Wanzhi,)

966
00:41:27,230 --> 00:41:28,190
(you're the youngest,)

967
00:41:29,510 --> 00:41:31,000
(yet you're big-hearted.)

968
00:41:32,030 --> 00:41:33,360
(College paid off.)

969
00:41:50,880 --> 00:41:51,400
Qian,

970
00:41:52,030 --> 00:41:53,070
why are you crying?

971
00:41:53,760 --> 00:41:54,590
What's wrong, Qian?

972
00:41:54,630 --> 00:41:55,590
Did someone bully you?

973
00:41:56,360 --> 00:41:57,800
Don't call me that.

974
00:41:58,030 --> 00:41:59,840
We're not that close.

975
00:42:03,400 --> 00:42:06,000
A college student is really different.

976
00:42:09,800 --> 00:42:10,760
How can you see

977
00:42:10,840 --> 00:42:12,630
what's in my heart?

978
00:42:13,400 --> 00:42:14,670
It's your fault.

979
00:42:15,360 --> 00:42:17,150
You made me cry.

980
00:42:19,150 --> 00:42:19,710
Enough.

981
00:42:20,360 --> 00:42:21,710
It's late. Quit the wailing.

982
00:42:22,960 --> 00:42:24,070
Or I'll kick you.

983
00:42:24,510 --> 00:42:26,480
So what? I'll cry if I want.

984
00:42:26,510 --> 00:42:27,710
I'm crying!

985
00:42:28,670 --> 00:42:29,710
Zhu! Stop!

986
00:42:30,840 --> 00:42:31,670
Why crying?

987
00:42:32,670 --> 00:42:33,510
It's late.

988
00:42:34,030 --> 00:42:34,960
The others will hear

989
00:42:35,440 --> 00:42:36,480
and get the wrong idea.

990
00:42:40,480 --> 00:42:41,070
Stop looking!

991
00:42:41,710 --> 00:42:42,280
Go to sleep!
